## Overview

Before getting elected to congress, Ciscomani attended the controversial far-right, religious training group Patriot Academy and served on the board for several years. Ciscomani even helped establish a branch of the Patriot Academy in Arizona. 

-   Patriot Academy opposed same-sex marriage and abortion, and had an anti-LGBTQ, anti-abortion, climate denier on its board. Patriot Academy also offered what it claimed were self-defense classes that taught children as young as 11 years-old how to shoot a gun.
-   Patriot Academy partnered with another far-right organization, Convention of States, that wanted to rewrite the U.S. constitution.
-   Far-right Republican congresswoman and embarrassment to Colorado, Lauren Boebert, was also a student of Patriot Academy.

## Ciscomani Had Close Ties To The Far-Right, Religious Training Group That Lauren Boebert Also Attended: Patriot Academy

### Ciscomani Attended the Patriot Academy And Served On The Board For Several Years Until His Election To Congress

**Ciscomani: “I Can Wholeheartedly Say That Nothing In My Life Has Given Me A Clearer Direction For My Life Than Patriot Academy.”** According to a blog post Juan Ciscomani wrote for the Patriot Academy, "Your next step is attending Patriot Academy. I can wholeheartedly say that nothing in my life has given me a clearer direction for my life than Patriot Academy – and I am not the only alum that feels this way.  The Lord may have called you into government and your Patriot Academy experience will definitely shine some light on your next steps." \[Juan Ciscomani, Blog – Patriot Press, [8/6/10](https://www.patriotacademy.com/youve-been-called/)\]

**2006-2008: Ciscomani Attended The Patriot Academy For Three Years.** According to The Patriot Academy, "Juan Ciscomani attended Patriot Academy in 2006, 2007, and 2008. Even though Juan had a degree in political science, PA revolutionized the very core of his beliefs about government."

#### Ciscomani Helped Bring The Patriot Academy To Arizona

**Ciscomani Was Responsible For Opening The Patriot Academy In Arizona.** According to the Copper Courier, “Ciscomani does not have ownership over Patriot Academy, although he has been a prominent leader of the far-right group as a board member, and is responsible for campuses opening in Arizona.” \[Copper Courier, [8/29/25](https://coppercourier.com/2024/08/29/ciscomani-patriot-academy-ad-tucson/)\]

**Ciscomani Brought The Academy To Arizona And Sat On The Board For 14 Years.** According to Cronkite News, "He attended again in 2007 and 2008, brought the program to Arizona in 2013, and sat on the board of directors for 14 years." \[Cronkite News, [7/25/24](https://cronkitenews.azpbs.org/2024/07/25/kirsten-engel-slams-juan-ciscomani-patriot-academy-christian-nationalist-group/)\]

**Patriot Academy Published A Blog Claiming Same-Sex Marriage Was A Sin.** According to a blog published by the Patriot Academy, "The sadness of it all is that the Church, which is supposed to be the bastion for Christ, His body and a safe place for His followers, has in many places turned into a spineless, indoctrinated, broken place.  Now do not get me wrong, I know all Churches are not like this.
